hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I read a lot deep numb anestesi Now we don’t build things (an exaggeration, of course: the UK’s manufacturing base is nowhere near as deflated as anti-Thatcher comedians would have you believe) but we still make money by selling “services”, such as public text messaging on the web. It’s baffling to me how that works, though, ontologically, I have to accept that it does (the concept of a multibillion-pound Twitter makes a multibillion-pound Twitter a reality). It’s no less weird than a mania for tulips, is it?
